# Escapar — Project Documentation

_Last updated: 2026-05-16_

This document describes the current, verified state of the codebase. Anything
that the code _expects_ but the database does not provide is called out
explicitly under "Known gaps" so contributors don't waste time tracing
ghost tables.

---

## 1. Product overview

Escapar is a vacation-rental property management SaaS. It serves three
audiences from a single React app:

1. **Internal team** (super-admin, admin/co_admin, cohost) — manages
   organizations, properties, bookings, tasks, staff.
2. **Field staff** (cleaner, driver, decorator, maintenance, staff) — a
   stripped-down task agenda on mobile.
3. **Guests** (public URLs at `/g/:slug`, `/s/:slug`, etc.) — view
   property info, services, coupons. No login required for most public
   guest pages.

The repository is named `abbiatti-com` for historical reasons and the
production URL is currently `abbiatti-com.vercel.app`. The product brand
is "Escapar", with a long-term plan to move to `escapar.net`.

---

## 2. Tech stack

| Layer | Choice |
|---|---|
| UI framework | React 18 + TypeScript |
| Bundler / dev server | Vite 5 (`@vitejs/plugin-react-swc`) |
| Styling | TailwindCSS 3 + shadcn/ui (Radix primitives) |
| Routing | `react-router-dom` v6 |
| Server state | `@tanstack/react-query` v5 |
| Forms | `react-hook-form` + `zod` |
| Backend | Supabase (Postgres, Auth, Storage, RLS) |
| i18n | `i18next` + `react-i18next` (FR / EN / AR) |
| QR codes | `qrcode.react` + `@yudiel/react-qr-scanner` |
| Tests | Vitest (unit), Playwright (E2E in `e2e/`) |
| Desktop wrap | Electron 41 (loads `dist/index.html` via `electron/main.cjs`) |
| Hosting | Vercel (SPA rewrites in `vercel.json`) |

The Supabase project id used in `src/integrations/supabase/client.ts` is
`pqaxxhateycrklzlnhkc.supabase.co` and the publishable key is hard-coded
in that file. There is currently no `.env.local` with `VITE_SUPABASE_*`
variables — the client is wired in directly. The root `.env` only holds
Playwright E2E credentials, not runtime config.

---

## 3. Repository layout

```
abbiatti-com/
├── src/
│   ├── App.tsx                  Routes + providers
│   ├── main.tsx                 Vite entry
│   ├── pages/                   One file per route
│   ├── components/              UI components (incl. shadcn/ui in components/ui)
│   ├── contexts/AuthContext.tsx Supabase session state
│   ├── hooks/                   useCohostKpis, use-mobile, use-toast
│   ├── integrations/supabase/   client.ts + auto-generated types.ts
│   ├── lib/                     access.ts, authRedirect.ts, billing.ts, …
│   ├── i18n/                    Translation files
│   └── assets/                  Logos, static images
├── supabase/migrations/         56+ SQL migration files (chronological)
├── e2e/                         Playwright specs
├── electron/main.cjs            Desktop shell
├── public/                      Static files served as-is
├── playwright.config.ts
├── vite.config.ts
├── tailwind.config.ts
├── vercel.json                  SPA fallback to /
└── CLAUDE.md                    AI-assistant guidance (rules + role map)
```

Root-level SQL files (`fix_user_roles.sql`, `restore_profiles_from_auth.sql`,
`restore_super_admin.sql`) are one-off **recovery scripts** run manually
in the Supabase SQL editor. They are NOT auto-applied by
`supabase db push` and are not part of the migration history.

---

## 4. Authentication and role model

### 4.1 The seven roles

`profiles.role` is a free-form `text` column. The values used by the app
are enumerated in `src/lib/access.ts`:

| Role | Bucket | Default landing route |
|---|---|---|
| `super_admin` | global admin | `/super-admin` |
| `admin` | org admin | `/admin/dashboard` |
| `co_admin` | org admin | `/admin/dashboard` |
| `cohost` | property-scoped manager | `/cohost/dashboard` |
| `cleaner` | field staff | `/employee` |
| `driver` | field staff | `/employee` |
| `decorator` | field staff | `/employee` |
| `maintenance` | field staff | `/employee` |
| `staff` | field staff | `/employee` |
| `guest` | external | `/guest` (forced redirect inside `AppLayout`) |

Helper sets exported from `access.ts`:
- `ADMIN_ROLES = ['super_admin', 'admin', 'co_admin']`
- `ORG_ADMIN_ROLES = ['admin', 'co_admin']`
- `EMPLOYEE_ROLES = ['cleaner', 'driver', 'decorator', 'maintenance', 'staff']`

Role detection has a small piece of inferred logic: a profile whose role
is something else but who has _at least one row in `property_cohosts`_ is
treated as a cohost for routing purposes (`getDashboardPathForRole`).

### 4.2 How a login becomes a dashboard

The route layer is intentionally simple — `ProtectedRoute` only checks
"is there a Supabase session?". It does **not** check roles. Role gating
happens inside the page or layout:

1. User logs in via `/auth` or `/staff-login` (QR / phone-based flow).
2. `AuthContext` writes the session into React state.
3. The user is routed to `/` (or whatever was stored in `postLoginRedirect`).
4. `src/pages/Home.tsx` calls `getUserAccess(user.id)` and
   `<Navigate>`s to the correct dashboard based on `profiles.role`.
5. Pages that only some roles may use (e.g. `SuperAdmin.tsx`) call
   `isSuperAdminUser()` themselves and render `<Unauthorized />`
   otherwise.

`AppLayout` reloads `getUserAccess` separately to decide which nav items
to show. Profiles with `role = 'guest'` are force-redirected to `/guest`.

### 4.3 Redirect handling

`src/lib/authRedirect.ts` implements a small state machine for
post-login redirects. It supports query strings (`?redirect=…`), router
state, and a TTL'd `sessionStorage` slot (10 minutes). It normalises and
same-origin-checks anything it reads. There's a debug flag at
`localStorage["debug:authRedirect"]`.

### 4.4 Per-role capability breakdown

The deep reference for each role — what they can **view**, **access**,
and **do** — lives in a dedicated companion file:

> **See [`roles.md`](./roles.md)** for the full per-role breakdown of
> super-admin, admin, co-admin, co-host, employee (cleaner / driver /
> decorator / maintenance / staff), and guest, plus a capability matrix.

The rest of this section retained for context. Where a feature is
broken because its underlying table is missing (§6.2) or because role
gating is incomplete (§4.2), that is called out in `roles.md` as well.

> **Caveat.** Because `ProtectedRoute` does not check roles, a logged-in
> user typing the URL of a page they shouldn't see will still render
> it. The only true enforcement today is (a) the sidebar's per-role nav,
> (b) the `Home.tsx` dispatcher, (c) the explicit `isSuperAdminUser`
> check on `/super-admin/*` and `/anomalies`, and (d) Supabase RLS.
> Anything below describes the *intended* permission model the UI is
> designed around.

#### 4.4.1 Super-admin (`role = 'super_admin'`)

Platform operator. One per Escapar deployment, not per agency. Unrestricted
cross-organisation access.

**Routes / sidebar.** Super-admin nav: Organisations, Profils, Properties,
Availability, Reservations, Tasks, Reports, Settings. Plus the entire admin
sidebar (super-admins inherit manager pages). Super-admin-only routes:

- `/super-admin` — list of every organisation on the platform.
- `/super-admin/orgs/:id` — single-org deep dive.
- `/super-admin/billing` — per-org pricing and invoices.
- `/super-admin/profiles` — every profile across every org.
- `/super-admin/staff` — internal platform staff (technician, developer,
  accountant, support, super_admin).

These five pages are the only ones with a server-checked role guard
(`isSuperAdminUser()` falling back to a `user_roles` query). Everything
else renders `<Unauthorized />` for non-super-admins.

**What they can view.** Every `organizations` row with status, trial
expiry, plan limits, and stat cards (total orgs, active, suspended).
For a single org: counts of admins, cohosts, employees, properties;
pending invitations; pricing config; full invoice history. Every
profile and every internal staff member across the platform.

**What they can do.**

- Create / edit / suspend / reactivate / delete an organisation
  (inserts and updates on `organizations`).
- Invite an admin into any org via the `create-team-member` edge
  function.
- Extend trials with `+7d` / `+30d` buttons (`trial_ends_at`).
- Configure pricing per org: `price_monthly_base`, `price_per_admin`,
  `price_per_cohost`, `price_per_employee`, `price_per_message`,
  `price_per_ical_sync`, `price_per_mb_storage`, `billing_currency`.
- Generate invoices via `computeUsageForOrg` → insert into `invoices`;
  download PDF, mark sent, mark paid, or delete each invoice.
- Cancel pending invitations (sets `profiles.invitation_status` to
  null).
- Assign any role to any profile (including promoting a profile to
  super_admin) via `SuperAdminProfiles`.
- Create platform-level internal staff via `SuperAdminStaff`.
- Everything an admin can do, scoped to any org.

**What they cannot do.** No functional restrictions in code; RLS
policies for super-admin generally bypass tenant matching via
`is_super_admin()`.

#### 4.4.2 Admin / Co-admin (`role = 'admin' | 'co_admin'`)

The agency owner or senior manager. Sees everything inside their own
organisation and nothing outside it. `admin` and `co_admin` are nearly
identical; differences are noted inline.

**Routes / sidebar.** Manager nav: Dashboard, Properties, Availability,
Reservations, Tasks, Reports, Team, Settings. Additional routes
reachable by URL or contextual links: `/inventory`, `/rentals`,
`/guest-books`, `/tickets`, `/anomalies`, `/showcase` (booking
requests), `/invoices`, `/cohosts/:id`.

Cannot access `/super-admin/*` — those routes render
`<Unauthorized />`.

**What they can view.**

- **Dashboard** — KPI cards scoped to their `org_id`: total properties,
  total team, total tasks. Includes the `WhatsAppReminders` panel
  (builds `wa.me` deeplinks; no real WhatsApp API).
- **Properties** — every property in their org with all private fields
  (`access_code`, `entry_instructions`). iCal sources, approval
  timeline, QR code.
- **Reservations / Availability** — full reservation list and calendar
  for the org.
- **Tasks** — every task in the org regardless of assignee.
- **Team** — every team member with role and assignment info, plus
  inline cohost KPIs.
- **Tickets** — every `maintenance_tickets` row filterable by status.
- **Anomalies** — overdue tasks, open tickets, unanswered messages,
  missed cleanings, reservation conflicts.
- **Reports** — generate PDFs filterable by year / month / property.
- **Invoices** — their org's own invoices owed to the platform
  (read-only, downloadable as PDF).

**What they can do.**

- Full CRUD on `properties`, `tasks`, `bookings/reservations`,
  `rental_items`, `items` (inventory), `guest_books`.
- Update `maintenance_tickets` status across new → in_progress →
  resolved → closed.
- Process booking requests from the public showcase.
- Invite team members via `create-team-member`:
  - **Admins** can invite: co_admin, cohost, cleaner, driver, decorator,
    maintenance.
  - **Co-admins** can invite: cohost, cleaner, driver, decorator,
    maintenance — **but not other co-admins or admins.**
- Promote or demote members within their tier (admins can edit anyone
  below them; co-admins cannot edit other co-admins).
- Generate and send WhatsApp template messages (deeplink-only).
- Generate PDF reports.
- Edit own profile, org settings, partner integrations, photo albums.

**What they cannot do.**

- Access any `/super-admin/*` route.
- Edit the super_admin role on any profile.
- See another organisation's data (queries are `org_id`-filtered and
  RLS-backed).
- Actually *send* WhatsApp messages — only deeplinks are built.

#### 4.4.3 Co-host (`role = 'cohost'`, or any profile with `property_cohosts` rows)

A property manager assigned to a subset of an organisation's
properties via `property_cohosts`. Sees only the properties they are
linked to and the data attached to those properties.

**Routes / sidebar.** Cohost nav: Dashboard, Properties, Availability,
Reservations, Tasks, Team, Rentals, Livrets (guest books), Signalements
(tickets). Notably **missing** from the cohost sidebar: Reports,
Settings, Anomalies, Inventory.

**Permission model.** Each `property_cohosts` row carries a
`permissions text[]` column. The tokens currently in use are
`manage_properties`, `manage_reservations`, `manage_tasks`,
`manage_staff`, `view_financials`, `manage_settings`. A cohost only
gets the actions explicitly granted on each property. Helpers:
`getPropertyPermissions(userId, propertyId)` and
`hasPropertyPermission(userId, propertyId, permission)` in
`access.ts`.

**What they can view.**

- **Dashboard** — KPI cards scoped to *their* assigned properties:
  number of assigned properties, total tasks across those properties,
  and distinct team members in `property_cohosts` for the same
  properties.
- **Properties** — only their assigned properties. Uses the
  "without-private-fields" select; sensitive fields like `access_code`
  may be hidden by RLS.
- **Reservations / Availability / Tasks** — limited to their
  properties.
- **Team** — visibility into the cohosts and employees who share their
  properties.
- **Rentals / Livrets / Signalements** — for their properties only.

**What they can do.** Subject to the per-property `permissions[]`:

- View and update property details.
- Create, update, and cancel reservations.
- Create, assign, and update tasks.
- Update guest books and `maintenance_tickets` for their properties.
- View their own KPI deep-dive (`/cohosts/:id`).

**What they cannot do.**

- Access `/super-admin/*` or `/anomalies` (admin-only).
- See pages absent from their sidebar (Reports, Settings, Inventory)
  without typing the URL — and RLS should empty them.
- Manage org-wide team roles — `Team.tsx` gives cohosts no editable
  roles. They can view but not promote or demote.
- See properties they are not assigned to.
- See financial data unless `view_financials` is in their per-property
  permissions.
- Extend trials, edit org settings, configure pricing, manage invoices.

#### 4.4.4 Employee — cleaner / driver / decorator / maintenance / staff

Field workers. All five employee roles share the **exact same UI** —
the role string is used to categorise team members and filter task
assignments, not to gate features.

**Routes / sidebar.** Staff nav (entire surface area):
Mon agenda, Signalements, Help, Settings. `/employee` and `/` redirect
to `MyAgenda` automatically.

**What they can view.**

- **My Agenda** (`src/pages/MyAgenda.tsx`) — the only operational page.
  Queries `tasks` filtered by `assigned_to = user.id` and
  `status != 'done'`, ordered by `due_at`. Tasks are grouped by Today /
  Tomorrow / future / undated, each with a type icon. Property name
  hydrated from `properties` for tasks with a `property_id`.
- **Signalements** — `/tickets` is reachable from the sidebar; RLS
  controls what they actually see.
- **Settings** — own profile only.
- **Help** — static help page.

The UI is intentionally simple per CLAUDE.md: big buttons, photo
uploads, voice recording. No dense tables.

**What they can do.**

- **Start a task** — sets status to `in_progress`, writes
  `started_at`.
- **Complete a task** — sets status to `done`, writes
  `completed_at`.
- **QR check-in** — `QRCheckInScanner` for `todo` tasks tied to a
  `property_id`.
- **Upload photos** for tasks (mobile-friendly upload to `task_photos`
  storage).
- **Update their own profile.**

**What they cannot do.**

- Create or assign tasks — only managers can.
- See other employees' tasks.
- View properties, reservations, the team list, reports, inventory,
  anomalies, or any admin/cohost page — those routes don't appear in
  their sidebar, and RLS should return empty results if hit directly.
- Change task status arbitrarily — only the `todo → in_progress →
  done` flow is exposed.
- Manage anyone — no Team page in their sidebar.

#### 4.4.5 Guest (`role = 'guest'`)

End-customer staying at a property. Authenticated separately and
routed to a dedicated portal that never shows the main app sidebar.
`AppLayout` auto-redirects any profile with `role = 'guest'` to
`/guest` with `replace: true`.

**Routes.**

- `/guest` — the guest portal for the currently logged-in guest.
- `/guest-preview/:reservationId` — same UI in preview mode for staff
  QA (admin / cohost only).
- Public, unauthenticated routes also accessible to anyone:
  - `/g/:slug` — printable guest book.
  - `/s/:slug` — public reservation page.
  - `/r/:slug` — issue-reporting form.
  - `/v/:orgId` — agency public showcase.
  - `/redeem/:code` — coupon redemption.

**What they can view.** `GuestPortal.tsx` re-checks the guest role via
`user_roles`, then loads:

- Their `guest_accounts` record (linked to a property and a
  reservation).
- Property details and the active `guest_books` entry for that
  property.
- Partner services (`partner_services` filtered to `active=true` and
  `visible_to_guest=true`, sorted gold → silver → standard).
- Rental items (`rental_items` filtered to `active=true`).
- Their own message thread with the host.
- Their own photo uploads.
- Coupons they hold.
- An `AdBanner` placement.

Typical tabs: Wi-Fi, key access, messages, photos (camera), partners,
rentals, coupons.

**What they can do.**

- Post messages to the host.
- Upload photos with comments.
- Browse partner services offered for their property.
- Browse rental items they can request.
- Redeem coupons.
- Sign out.

**What they cannot do.**

- See any property or reservation other than their own.
- View tasks, the team, or any operational data.
- Access the main app sidebar or any admin / cohost / employee page —
  the auto-redirect on every navigation prevents it.

#### 4.4.6 Capability matrix — quick lookup

| Capability | Super-admin | Admin | Co-admin | Co-host | Employee | Guest |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| Manage organisations (CRUD) | yes | no | no | no | no | no |
| Configure org pricing & invoices | yes | no | no | no | no | no |
| Suspend / reactivate orgs | yes | no | no | no | no | no |
| Invite admins | yes | yes | no | no | no | no |
| Invite cohosts | yes | yes | yes | no | no | no |
| Invite employees | yes | yes | yes | no | no | no |
| CRUD properties | yes | yes (own org) | yes (own org) | yes (assigned + permitted) | no | no |
| CRUD reservations / bookings | yes | yes (own org) | yes (own org) | yes (assigned) | no | no |
| CRUD tasks | yes | yes (own org) | yes (own org) | yes (assigned) | update own only | no |
| Generate PDF reports | yes | yes | yes | no | no | no |
| View anomalies dashboard | yes | yes | yes | no | no | no |
| Manage inventory | yes | yes | yes | no | no | no |
| Manage guest books | yes | yes | yes | yes (assigned) | no | no |
| View own agenda | n/a | n/a | n/a | n/a | yes | n/a |
| Use guest portal | no | preview only | preview only | no | no | yes |

